import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Ancient Rome — Latin Origin Words That Score"
  description="Roman and Latin origin words valid in Scrabble with point values. FORUM 10pts, VETO 7pts, APEX 13pts, TOGA 5pts. Classical vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble roman words, latin scrabble words, forum scrabble points, veto scrabble word, apex scrabble, toga scrabble, ancient rome words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Ancient Rome — Latin Origin Words That Score","description":"Roman and Latin origin words valid in Scrabble with point values. FORUM 10pts, VETO 7pts, APEX 13pts, TOGA 5pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-ancient-rome"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is APEX a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! APEX scores 13 points (A=1, P=3, E=1, X=8). It means the highest point or tip of something. The X tile provides 8 of the 13 points, making it a compact high-value play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is FORUM worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FORUM scores 10 points (F=4, O=1, R=1, U=1, M=3). It refers to a Roman public square used for meetings. The F and M tiles provide most of the scoring power."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is VETO valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. VETO scores 7 points (V=4, E=1, T=1, O=1) and means to reject or prohibit. Originally a Latin word meaning 'I forbid', used by Roman tribunes. The V tile provides over half the score."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Ancient Rome — Latin Origin Words That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Ancient Rome gave us words we still use daily — and many of them score surprisingly well in Scrabble. APEX delivers 13 points from just 4 tiles thanks to the X, FORUM uses both F and M for double mid-value scoring, and VETO is a reliable V-tile outlet. Latin-origin words are easy to remember because they're part of everyday English.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">APEX (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FORUM</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">VETO</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TOGA</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Roman Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">APEX — 13 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">A=1, P=3, E=1, X=8 · 4 letters · X power word</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The highest point or pinnacle. APEX scores 3.25 points per tile — among the best ratios for any 4-letter word. The X tile does the heavy lifting while A, P, and E are all common tiles you'll frequently have available.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏛️ FORUM</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · F=4, O=1, R=1, U=1, M=3 · Public square</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚫 VETO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · V=4, E=1, T=1, O=1 · To prohibit</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👘 TOGA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · T=1, O=1, G=2, A=1 · Roman garment</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚔️ GLADIUS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · G=2, L=1, A=1, D=2, I=1, U=1, S=1 · Roman sword</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Latin Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CENSUS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VILLA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AURA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAMPUS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CONSUL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">APEX is a 4-letter X word:</span> Most X words are 5+ letters. APEX fits in tight spaces and scores 13 points. On a double-word square that's 26 points from just 4 tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FORUM uses F and M together:</span> Both F (4pts) and M (3pts) are mid-value tiles. FORUM plays them both in one word for 10 points, clearing your rack of two harder-to-place consonants simultaneously.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">VETO hooks to VETOES:</span> VETO is a quick V dump at 7 points. It extends naturally to VETOES (8pts) or VETOED (10pts) on subsequent turns if the board allows it.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Latin-origin words tend to be <span class="text-white font-medium">short and tile-efficient</span>. APEX (3.25 pts/tile), VETO (1.75 pts/tile), and FORUM (2.0 pts/tile) all use common letters alongside one premium tile, making them reliable plays you'll have the tiles for.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/foreign-origin-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Foreign Origin Words in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/historical-terms-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Historical Terms in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble</span></a>
        
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-vikings/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Vikings</span></a>

          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-volcanism/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Volcanism</span></a>
</div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid Latin-origin word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
